cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SD

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with grammar induction and parsing, which are core topics in natural language processing.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of Bayesian PCFG inducer, which is a machine learning technique.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with unsupervised learning of grammars, which is a subfield of AI.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of depth-bounding to limit the search space of the inducer, which is a technique related to algorithms and data structures.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the implementation of the depth-bounding technique within a chart-based Bayesian PCFG inducer.
